\f4\b0\fs28 \cf2 \'95
\f2\b\fs36  Constructing a primer list\
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li576\ri-19445
\cf6 \
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li576\ri-19445

\b0\fs28 \cf0 You can make your primer list right within 
\i Amplify
\i0 , but it's probably easier to use another program, such as a spreadsheet or text editor. You can even use a word processor, provided you use the option to save as plain text. Regardless of what software you use, the end result should be a plain text file where each primer is on a separate line, and the columns are separated by tabs. Alternatively, it can be a "csv" or "comma-separated value" file where the columns are delimited by commas and the file extension is .csv. \
\
The order of the columns should be the same as in the primer list. That is: Sequence - Name - Notes. If you have a primer list with a different order, it is easy to change it within a spreadsheet program when columns can be dragged to any desired order.\
\

\i Amplify4
\i0  can open primer lists made with earlier versions of 
\i Amplify
\i0 .\
\
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li270\ri-19445

\f4 \cf2 \'95
\f2\b\fs36  Selecting versus "checking" primers\
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li576\ri-19445

\b0\fs28 \cf0 \
In the example shown above, the primer named "BCD" is selected whereas two others, "bif16" and "BPg" are checked. The difference is that those with a check-mark will be used in the PCR simulation whereas the selected primers are the ones affected by copying, editing, etc.\
\
You can select multiple primers by dragging over them, or by holding down the 
\f1 \uc0\u8984 
\f2  key while clicking the primer rows. The selected primers do not have to be contiguous in the list.\
\
Primers can be checked simply by clicking in the checkbox on the left, or by selecting them and choosing 
\b Check
\b0  from the 
\b Selected
\b0  popup menu.\
\
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li270\ri-19445

\f4 \cf2 \'95
\f2\b\fs36  Copying and pasting primers and rearranging the list\
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li576\ri-19445

\b0\fs28 \cf0 \
Copying and pasting primers works as you would expect it to. When you choose 
\b Copy
\b0  (
\f1 \uc0\u8984 
\f2 -C) all the selected primers are placed on the clipboard, even if the selected primers are not contiguous in the list. The 
\b Cut
\b0  command (
\f1 \uc0\u8984 
\f2 -X) is the same except that the selected primers are also removed from the list.\
\
Once you have copied a set of primers onto the clipboard, you can 
\b Paste 
\b0 them (
\f1 \uc0\u8984 
\f2 -V) into a spreadsheet program, a text editor or to another position in your 
\i Amplify
\i0  primer list. If you 
\b Paste
\b0  them into the primer list, they will go above the first selected primer.\
\
You can also copy primers from a text editor or spreadsheet program and paste them into 
\i Amplify
\i0 . Pasting works the same way.\
\

\i Hint:
\i0  Here is a way to collect a group of primers from anywhere in your list and move them to a single location. First select them all using 
\f1 \uc0\u8984 
\f2 -clicking or dragging. Next, cut them to the clipboard with 
\f1 \uc0\u8984 
\f2 -X. Finally, select the position you want move them to, and use 
\f1 \uc0\u8984 
\f2 -V.\
\
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li270\ri-19445

\f4 \cf2 \'95
\f2\b\fs36  Editing individual primers\
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li576\ri-19445

\b0\fs28 \cf0 \
To edit a particular primer, first select it by clicking on it. Then hit the tab key to begin editing the sequence. If you want to edit the name, hit the tab key again, and so on.\
\
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li270\ri-19445

\f4 \cf2 \'95
\f2\b\fs36  Adding and removing rows from the primer list\
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li576\ri-19445

\b0\fs28 \cf0 \
Use the "+" button above the primer list to add a new blank primer above the selected row. The "-" button removes all selected primers. (Note: Using the "-" button differs from the 
\b Cut
\b0  command as it does not place the deleted primers onto the clipboard.)\
\
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li270\ri-19445

\f4 \cf2 \'95
\f2\b\fs36  Flipping primer sequences\
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li576\ri-19445

\b0\fs28 \cf0 \
When you hit the 
\f5 \uc0\u55357 \u56580 
\f2  button above the primer list, the sequences of all selected primers will be flipped. That is, the order of bases will be reversed and each base replaced by its complement. The flipping operation handles any ambiguous base codes correctly, and preserves upper- and lower-cases. Hitting the 
\f5 \uc0\u55357 \u56580 
\f2  button again restores the original sequence.\cf2 \
\cf0 \
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li270\ri-19445

\f4 \cf2 \'95
\f2\b\fs36  Searching the primer list\
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li576\ri-19445

\b0\fs28 \cf0 \
If you select 
\b Find
\b0  from the 
\b Edit
\b0  menu or hit 
\f1 \uc0\u8984 
\f2 -F you can enter a string for searching.\
