\fs28 \cf0 The method used by 
\i Amplify
\i0  is two dimensional. It computes two distinct attributes for each potential primer match, and displays the match only if each criterion exceed its pre-set threshold. If they do, the match is included, and the size of the arrow drawn on the map reflects the sum of the two quantities.\
\
The two quantities are called "primability" and "stability." The difference is that the former gives most of the weight to base matches near the 3\uc0\u8242  end, thus enabling the match to behave as a good PCR primer. The second weights each base match according to the length of run it is in. Thus, this quantity reflects the overall stability of the primer-target bond.\
\
Both quantities make use of a table of pair scores to assign a numerical value to each potential base pairing. The default values for these scores are shown below, but they can be changed in the settings.\
\
