\f1\b0\fs32 \cf11 \uc0\u9642 \u65038 
\f2\b  Q: 
\b0 What is the source of the algorithms and parameters used for evaluating primer matches?\

\b\fs28 \cf2 \
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li27\fi446\ri-19445

\fs32 \cf0 A:
\fs28  
\b0 It\'92s all pretty much trial-and-error. I tested a variety of algorithmic approaches, and found that the two-dimensional approach with separate quantities for 
\i primability 
\i0 and 
\i stability 
\i0 worked for all the PCR runs in my lab. Once I found a workable method, it produced reliable results through many years, several postdocs and a variety of protocols used in my lab. If you find that 
\i Amplify\'92s
\i0  predictions don\'92t match your results, you can tinker with the parameters in the settings window. When you find a combination that works for you, you can save it as your defaults. (Don\'92t worry, you can always restore the original settings.) You can also share your settings with others by saving them in a file. All these options are in the 
\b Preferences\'85
\b0  window.\
\
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li270\ri-19445

\f1\fs32 \cf11 \uc0\u9642 \u65038 
\f2\b  Q: 
\b0 How does this version differ from version 3.x?\

\b\fs28 \cf2 \
\pard\tx6480\pardeftab720\li27\fi446\ri-19445

\fs32 \cf0 A:
\fs28  
\b0 The basic algorithms are still the same, and I have tried to keep the essential user interface elements similar.
\b \
\

\b0 Version 4 was completely re-written in a language that should be more easily maintained as the MacOS evolves. Version 4 is in the 
\i Swift
\i0  programming language, which is much more widely used than the other languages I have used for previous versions of 
\i Amplify
\i0 . \
\
Here are a few changes you might notice:\
\
\'96 Split screens are now used to keep the two kinds of substrate -- target and primers -- together in one window, and the two kinds of results -- graphic map and textual output -- in another.\
\
\'96 Amplify will automatically reopen your last-used primer and target files. (You can turn this feature off.) An \'93Open Recent\'94 menu item is also included.\
\
\'96 Length limitations on the target sequence and primers have been removed.\
\
\'96 Parallel processing is now employed for better performance on multi-core computers.\
\
\'96 Opening target and primer files is simplified so that both kinds of file can be opened at once from the same dialog. (
\i Amplify
\i0  can tell whether a file contains primers or a target.)\
\
\'96 Cutting and pasting primers and primer lists is more robust. You can use the clipboard to move primers around within 
\i Amplify\'92s
\i0  primer list, or to and from spreadsheet programs.\
\
\'96 Styled text is used in the output to make the results more readable. You can also save this styled text in \'93rich text format\'94.\
\
\'96 The online help has been expanded and combined. It also has a 
\b Topics
\b0  popup menu and another for 
\b Frequently Asked Questions.
\b0 \
\
